          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
<p>As part of Los Angeles Mayor Eric Garcetti’s, plan to “increase transparency,” he opened a platform with open data so the public can have access to Crime Data from 2010 to present with information provided by the Los Angeles Police Department. This data showed when the crime occurred and the date it was reported; as well as the criminal code, location, time and information about the victim.</p>
 
<p>By analyzing the data from 1,621,438 crime incidents, dated from April 10, 2010 to November 7, 2017, we can see that simple assault battery is the most common crime with 149,000 crime incidents. This was followed by burglary from a vehicle and stolen vehicles with 124,000 crime incidents, general burglary with 117,000 crime incidents, and plain petty theft ($950 & under) with 116,000 crime incidents.
</p>
